Other Improvements to Scope Allocation

Align carbon accounting with the Greenhouse Gas (GHG) Protocol by accurately allocating emissions to the correct scope for leased vehicles and for employees working from home (stationary assets).

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions with the Net Zero Cloud Starter or Growth license.

Why: These improvements help with GHG Protocol compliance and make sure that scope allocation to GHG scopes is accurate for leased vehicles and employees working from home.

To set the scope allocation in the vehicle asset emissions source to allocate emissions from leased vehicles to Scope 3, Category 13 (Downstream Leased Assets), use the Total Scope 3 Downstream Leased Assets picklist value in Carbon Emissions Scope Allocation of Vehicle Asset Emissions Source. 

To set scope allocation in the stationary asset environmental source to allocate emissions from employees working from home, use the Scope 3 Employee Commuting picklist value in Fuel Type Allocation of Carbon Emissions Scope Allocation Value.
title: Improvements to Scope Allocation for GHG Protocol Compliance
